RACE.FOOTNOTES: DR. ROGER pressed the early pace three wide, then dueled for the lead on the turn and made a two wide bid to be clear by the quarter pole, then drew out off the turn and then was ridden out to the wire to maintain a safe margin to the wire. VEGAS PLAYBOY was bumped at the start, settled on the inside, shifted out leaving the quarter pole and came three wide into the lane and closed well, second best. CATCHHIMANDFREEHIM hopped at the start and was off slowly, saved ground on the turn and swung out five wide leaving the turn and rallied. NATURE OFTHE BEAST chased the pace five wide and was four to five wide on the turn and had no rally. RACE.FOOTNOTES: EGO MAN tracked the early pace towards the inside, eased out on the turn and was three wide nearing the quarter pole, was blocked and angled in nearing the upper stretch and made a inside bid leaving the turn and took over nearing the furlong marker and edged away to prove best, driving. SHACKS WAY set a pressured pace in the two path, then dueled for the lead on the turn and gave way grudgingly.
